Tail
====

16-Oct-2005
~~~~~~~~~~~
Can get ROX-CLib via 0launch.

12-Oct-2005
~~~~~~~~~~~
Update for ROX-CLib changes, many externally visible symbols
(functions and types) now have rox_ or ROX prefixes.

11-Sep-2005
~~~~~~~~~~~
Remove aclocal.m4, replace with rox-clib.m4 and aclocal -I .

27-May-2005
~~~~~~~~~~~
Use apsymbols for Linux portability.

14-Nov-2004 (2.1.2)
~~~~~~~~~~~
Use new ROX-CLib features.

2.1.1
-----
Updated compilation system to use libdir.
Don't show more that 256KB when loading file (doesn't work via stdin).

2.1.0
-----
Use ROX-CLib 2.1.0, including aclocal.m4.
Stock icons in the menu.

2.0.0
-----
Stable release to go with ROX-CLib 2.0.0.

1.3.3
-----
Test out some new ROX-CLib interfaces (rox_init, info_win_new_from_appinfo).
Support for translating strings.
Set window icon.

1.3.2
-----
Fix the autocompilation broke in 1.3.1
Safer way to parse ROX-CLib's version number by Christopher Arndt.

1.3.1
-----
Italian translation of AppInfo provided by Yuri Bongiorno.
New icon provided by Geoff Youngs.  Look for PNG icons for the save box.

1.3.0
-----
Convert to GTK2.

1.2.2
-----
Fix for compilation problems with spaces in paths.

1.2.1
-----
Make sure AppRun can find rox_run.

1.2.0
-----
Stable release.

1.1.2
-----
Added -h and -v options.

1.1.1
-----
Small changes to compilation system.

1.1.0
-----
Switch over to ROX-CLib.
Can specify a title with -t option.
Add a status line giving time & date of last update, suppress with -c.

1.0.0
-----
Stable version.  (No changes from 0.1.7).

0.1.7
-----
Fix drag & drop code to avoid double drops.

0.1.6
-----
Updated menu code.  Reads <Choices>/Tail/gtkrc.

0.1.5
-----
Better debug output.  Save menu accelerators.  Scrolling to end of
window back in, unless truncated.

0.1.4
-----
Fixed bug in memory management.

0.1.3
-----
Use a pop-up menu.

0.1.2
-----
Disable the debug output.  I tried to monitor the file it itself was appending
to...

0.1.1
-----
Don't include sys/filio.h if it isn't there.
Remove code that scrolled to end of window, because it core dumped.
Report error if file can't be read.
